Where is the Dry Ice?

The dry ice can be found in Abbott 334. The dry ice is supplied by the department as a whole. Members of the Sisodia lab (which Silas claims does not exist), in room Ab330 can be asked for access.

Problems with Milli-Q water purifier?

In Feb 2020, Milli-Q started giving a water resistivity of 12-14 Mohm per cm instead of the usual 18 Mohm cm.
Email David White: dmwhite@bsd.uchicago.edu
Apparently, The Department of Neurology is in charge of replacing the cartiges for that machine. They like to allow the cartridge to last beyond technical expiration to save money. This is fine but David will respond promptly if you tell him the resistivity is off.


